                            <comment id="13092371" author="alangates" created="Sat, 27 Aug 2011 20:50:07 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch contains:&lt;br/&gt;
1) a Whirr properties file that will instantiate a small cluster for testing;&lt;br/&gt;
2) a shell script that will configure an EC2 machine with the appropriate packages, checkout Pig, apply a patch, and run the tests;&lt;br/&gt;
3) a README on how to use the preceding&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Whirr sold separately&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13093544" author="daijy" created="Tue, 30 Aug 2011 09:15:57 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Works for me. Need to mention:&lt;br/&gt;
1. Tested with whirr 0.6. It fails in my first try with whirr 0.4&lt;br/&gt;
2. I need to install svn and DBI by myself&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+1 for commit.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
